WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Our scripture reading this morning is Luke 24, 13-35.

2
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.000
It is printed in your worship guide if you would like to read along.

3
00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Let's listen carefully for this is the Word of God.

4
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.000
That very day, two of them were going to a village named Amias,

5
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:20.000
about seven miles from Jerusalem,

6
00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:25.000
and they were talking with each other about all these things that had happened.

7
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:30.000
While they were talking and discussing together, Jesus himself journeyed and went with them,

8
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.000
but their eyes were kept from recognizing him.

9
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.000
And he said to them,

10
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:40.000
what is this conversation that you are holding with each other as you walk?

11
00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:42.000
And they stood looking sad.

12
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:47.000
Then one of them named Cleopas answered him,

13
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:53.000
are you the only visitor to Jerusalem who does not know the things that have happened here in these days?

14
00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.000
And he said to him, what things?

15
00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:01.000
And they said to him concerning Jesus of Nazareth, a man who was a prophet,

16
00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:06.000
mighty indeed, and word before God and all the people.

17
00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:14.000
And how our chief priests and rulers delivered him up to the condemned to death and crucified him.

18
00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:20.000
But we had hoped that he was the one to redeem Israel.

19
00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
Yes, and besides all this, it is now the third day.

20
00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:30.000
Since these things happened, moreover, some women of our company amazed us.

21
00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:36.000
They were at the tomb early in the morning, and when they did not find his body,

22
00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:43.000
they came back saying that they had even seen a vision of angels who said that he was alive.

23
00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Some of those who were with us went to the tomb and found it just as the women had said.

24
00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:54.000
But him they did not see.

25
00:01:54.000 --> 00:02:00.000
And he said to them, oh foolish ones and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken.

26
00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:05.000
Has it not necessary that the Christ should suffer these things and enter into his glory?

27
00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:14.000
And in the beginning with Moses and the prophets, he interpreted to them in all scriptures the things concerning himself.

28
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:17.000
So they drew near to the village to which they were going.

29
00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:21.000
He acted as if he were going farther.

30
00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:28.000
But they urged him strongly saying, stay with us for it is toward evening and the day is now fast bent.

31
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:30.000
So he went to stay with them.

32
00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:42.000
When he was at table with them, he took the bread and blessed and broke it and gave it to them.

33
00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:50.000
And their eyes were opened and they recognized him and he vanished from the sight.

34
00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:58.000
They said to each other, did our hearts not burn within us while he walked, while he talked to us on the road, while he opened us to the scriptures.

35
00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:02.000
And they rose that same hour and returned to Jerusalem.

36
00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:10.000
And they found the eleven and those who were with them gathered together saying, the Lord has risen indeed when has appeared to Simon.

37
00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:16.000
Then they told what had happened on the road and how he was known to them in the breaking of the bread.

38
00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:18.000
This is the word of the Lord.

39
00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:28.000
Let's pray together, shall we?

40
00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:38.000
Lord, as you drew near to your disciples on that day, we pray that you would draw near to us.

41
00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:44.000
Lord, I pray that you would open up the scriptures to us, that we might behold wonderful things there.

42
00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
We pray this in Jesus' name. Amen.

43
00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:54.000
Well, this past Wednesday, I'm sure many of us witnessed a remarkable journey that began.

44
00:03:54.000 --> 00:04:01.000
I'm talking about Artemis 2. I don't know if you saw the space shuttle take off with its four-person crew.

45
00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:05.000
The plan is for it to be a ten-day journey around the moon.

46
00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:11.000
If they are successful, this will be the farthest that humans have ever traveled into space.

47
00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:21.000
And actually on the way back, they could very well be the fastest humans who've ever traveled in history as well as they make their way back to Earth.

48
00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:27.000
So I can't imagine what it must be like for them at the moment, wherever it is that they are at.

49
00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:31.000
Well, this morning, I want us to go on a journey.

50
00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:39.000
This text invites us on a journey that is far more exciting even than what is taking place right now with Artemis.

51
00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:47.000
It may not seem all that amazing at the start. As we're looking at the very start of the passage, you've got two ordinary disciples.

52
00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:56.000
One is called Cleopas. You've got, they're traveling down an ordinary road to a little place called Emmaus.

53
00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:02.000
So we might wonder what is so extraordinary about what is going on in this passage in front of us.

54
00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:11.000
Well, the extraordinary thing is not where they go but who it is who comes to them on their journey.

55
00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:19.000
Because we're told in verse 15 that as they traveled down the road, Jesus himself drew near.

56
00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:34.000
It's been three days since his crucifixion and they were certain that he was dead, but in actual fact as of that day, he was alive and well as he is still today.

57
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:39.000
But not only was he alive, he was right there with them.

58
00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:41.000
Extraordinary.

59
00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:48.000
And this passage is recorded for us here. Not that we just might know the fact about the resurrection, that Jesus really is risen from the dead.

60
00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:53.000
This story is here that we might know the risen Christ himself.

61
00:05:53.000 --> 00:06:06.000
So wherever you're at in your journey, whether you're a questioning skeptic or convinced believer or somewhere in between, I pray that you too would know this Christ who drew near to them.

62
00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:16.000
And that we would all be able to join together, saying from our hearts, as we did at the start of the service, Christ is risen. He is risen indeed.

63
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
So as we join the disciples on this journey, we're going to look at three different things.

64
00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
Simple things. One, we're going to look at how Jesus found them.

65
00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:27.000
Secondly, we're going to look at what Jesus showed them.

66
00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:30.000
And then lastly, I want us to see the way that it changed them.

67
00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:36.000
So notice with me how Jesus found them there in those early verses, verses 13 to 24.

68
00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:41.000
And by that, I don't mean like how Jesus found them, like as in like found out where they were at.

69
00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:45.000
I mean, what was the state that Jesus found them in?

70
00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:53.000
As we read here, we see that they were in a state of confusion, a state of disorientation and even grief.

71
00:06:53.000 --> 00:07:03.000
When you get to verse 17, at the very end, you see that there is a visible, visceral sadness that you can see as the disciples are standing there.

72
00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:10.000
So what's happened? And that's the very question that Jesus asks as he draws near.

73
00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:16.000
So let's lay it aside for a second the fact that Jesus is talking to them and they don't recognize that it's Jesus.

74
00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:18.000
But we'll return to that in just a moment.

75
00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:23.000
But let's see, as Jesus draws near, he asks them what they were talking about and what happens.

76
00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:28.000
And their answer gives us some insight as to why they are so discouraged.

77
00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:36.000
First of all, they say, well, Mr. you must be the only person in Jerusalem who doesn't know what has taken place.

78
00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:43.000
Another side note, this reminds us of the public nature of Jesus and his crucifixion.

79
00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:47.000
This wasn't something that happened in secret somewhere. This was a very public event.

80
00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:53.000
So that's why we can read about it in these eyewitness testimonies that we have in the Bible.

81
00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:57.000
But it's also, you know, you can look at non-Christian sources as well.

82
00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:05.000
Historians like Josephus, the Jewish historian or Tacitus, the Roman historian to see that it was known that Jesus really existed

83
00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:08.000
and that he really died.

84
00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:13.000
But Jesus draws their thoughts out further and says, what things, what happened?

85
00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:18.000
So they told him about, well, we're talking about what happened to Jesus.

86
00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:21.000
They talk about who Jesus is in verse 19.

87
00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:25.000
He was a man from Nazareth, but he wasn't just any man.

88
00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:30.000
He was a prophet. He was mighty both in the things that he said and the things that he did

89
00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:36.000
and his teaching and in his miracles. He was mighty before God and before all the people.

90
00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:43.000
So he was a man, but he wasn't an ordinary man. He was clearly a man of God and everyone could see his uniqueness.

91
00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:48.000
Then let's talk about what happened to him when you get to verse 20. This has really thrown them.

92
00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:58.000
They talk about how their leaders, the religious authorities of the day, had him executed, condemned to death, crucified.

93
00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:03.000
And they had hopes that he was going to redeem Israel, but this dashed their hope.

94
00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:07.000
By the way, when it talks about redeeming Israel here, this is Exodus language.

95
00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:11.000
For those of you who've been here recently, we've been going through the book of Exodus together.

96
00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:17.000
So here's their hope. They're hoping that this Jesus is like Moses, this mighty prophet.

97
00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:20.000
They're hoping that God is going to use him like he used Moses.

98
00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:27.000
Remember, Moses, God used him to lead God's people out of slavery in Egypt and onto the promised land.

99
00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:30.000
And here's the hope. They're under Roman occupation.

100
00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:33.000
They're hoping Jesus is going to deliver them from that.

101
00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:39.000
He's going to bring them out of that. And he's going to establish God's eternal kingdom in that way.

102
00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:44.000
And so they're hoping in that, but now he's gone.

103
00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:52.000
Back in 1986, there was another shuttle that took off the Challenger.

104
00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:58.000
Now that was a really sad occasion because he had so many people who were excited about the day

105
00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:04.000
and they all gathered together, many children gathered as well because he had a teacher who was going to go up in space.

106
00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:06.000
She was the first teacher who was going to do that.

107
00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:10.000
And so everybody was watching on as it shot off into space.

108
00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:17.000
Only seconds later, they then watched it as it disintegrated in the sky and made its way back down.

109
00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:19.000
Imagine the shock.

110
00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:22.000
Imagine the shock of Jesus' disciples here.

111
00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:25.000
Just a few days ago, I mean, things were really looking up.

112
00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:28.000
They were on the journey to Jerusalem.

113
00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:31.000
Even last Sunday, we saw that they were cheering.

114
00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:35.000
They were shouting Hosanna as their king rode into Jerusalem.

115
00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:38.000
Hope was alive and well.

116
00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:43.000
But now it's a journey, not to Jerusalem, but from Jerusalem.

117
00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:45.000
Things are very different.

118
00:10:45.000 --> 00:10:51.000
See, not only was the king crucified, their hope was dying with him.

119
00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:56.000
Sure, some of their number, they say, were claiming that the tomb was empty.

120
00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:59.000
They'd heard from some of the women saying that they had seen angels,

121
00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:03.000
but they describe it here as a vision of angels.

122
00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:06.000
It didn't seem plausible to say the least.

123
00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:09.000
You can hear the doubt and what the disciples say here.

124
00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:14.000
I want you to notice that they speak about hope in the past tense there in verse 21.

125
00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:18.000
We had hoped.

126
00:11:18.000 --> 00:11:23.000
They're speaking about Jesus in the past tense and hope in the past tense as well.

127
00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:30.000
I'm sure we all know what it's like to live with hope in the past tense.

128
00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:32.000
What do you think for a second?

129
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:37.000
Maybe you had a vision for your life and what it would look like by now.

130
00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:45.000
It would be a vision for marriage and your children and how that would be or maybe a career.

131
00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:48.000
We can name any number of things because we think about the future.

132
00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:51.000
We've got this vision for what we want our lives to be.

133
00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:54.000
And if you're a believer, you think, well, and I've got Jesus as well.

134
00:11:54.000 --> 00:12:02.000
And surely he is the one who's going to fulfill this vision that I have for my life.

135
00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:07.000
But then you find that things aren't exactly as you hoped they would be.

136
00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:09.000
Your hope is now past tense.

137
00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:14.000
It is no longer, I hope it is, I had hoped.

138
00:12:14.000 --> 00:12:20.000
And maybe in the sadness of that, your vision of Jesus is even clouded by that fog.

139
00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:22.000
You wanted him to take you there.

140
00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:24.000
What does that say about him?

141
00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:31.000
The thing that we need to see here in the passage is that right in the middle of the disciples' discouragement.

142
00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:34.000
Jesus draws near.

143
00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:40.000
You see, we don't see or rather they don't see Jesus, but he is there.

144
00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:42.000
So what does Jesus do in their discouragement?

145
00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:44.000
He draws near.

146
00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:47.000
And this is exactly what he does with us.

147
00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:53.000
We may not know what he is doing, but we can know that he is with us by faith.

148
00:12:53.000 --> 00:13:00.000
So Psalm 34, verse 18 says the Lord draws near to the brokenhearted.

149
00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:04.000
And he saves those who are crushed in spirit.

150
00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:10.000
So let me say this morning, whether your hope for your life feels alive or it feels dead,

151
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:15.000
whether you sense the Lord's presence or not, he is near.

152
00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:16.000
He draws near.

153
00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:17.000
He is here.

154
00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:21.000
And this is just as true in the dark as it is in the light.

155
00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:22.000
He is present.

156
00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:24.000
He draws near to the brokenhearted.

157
00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:30.000
So what does he do for them when he draws near to them in their discouragement?

158
00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:33.000
Let's see verses 25 to 31.

159
00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:36.000
Here we see that Jesus steps into the darkness.

160
00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:41.000
Yes, he is near, but he also gives them a light to guide their path.

161
00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:46.000
He renews their hope by way of revelation.

162
00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:48.000
And what does he reveal?

163
00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:51.000
He makes himself known to them.

164
00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:53.000
The thing that they need to see is him.

165
00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:55.000
And this is what he reveals to them.

166
00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.000
This is what he shows them himself.

167
00:13:57.000 --> 00:14:00.000
And he does this in a way that you might not expect.

168
00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:06.000
I mean, you might think, well, if that was me, I would have said, well, surprise, it's me, Jesus, I'm here.

169
00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:08.000
He would have just come right out and said who he was.

170
00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:13.000
I've risen from the dead just like I told you I was.

171
00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:15.000
But that's not how Jesus makes himself known.

172
00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:17.000
How does he do it?

173
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:22.000
When you get to verse 25, you see that he opens the scriptures to them.

174
00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:28.000
He says, oh foolish ones and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken.

175
00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:31.000
Now that might feel abrupt.

176
00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:36.000
Foolish ones, slow of heart, but know that he is saying this to them in love.

177
00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:41.000
And he is speaking in a way that is direct, in a way that kind of cuts right through the fog

178
00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:47.000
and brings them to a place of clarity in the midst of their confusion.

179
00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:50.000
He says, listen, this is what you need to hear.

180
00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:54.000
And he brings them to the Word of God.

181
00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:58.000
He says, I'm going to tell you about all that the prophets have spoken.

182
00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:00.000
This is where you're going to see what you need to see.

183
00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:02.000
So let's continue.

184
00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:08.000
Was it not necessary that the Christ should suffer these things and enter into his glory?

185
00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:14.000
He says, as we look at the scriptures, we're going to see that my death was all part of God's plan.

186
00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:19.000
This was planned all along, even if it wasn't part of your plan.

187
00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:23.000
A couple of weeks ago, our family, we traveled down to Gulf Shores together.

188
00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:27.000
And it wasn't the first time that we've done this, but I just know that Gulf Shores is in Alabama

189
00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:29.000
and you travel kind of straight down to it.

190
00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:33.000
So I'm driving down the road and we've got music playing, having a great time.

191
00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:36.000
And as I'm driving down the road, all of a sudden we pass this sign,

192
00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:38.000
welcome to Florida.

193
00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:41.000
And I absolutely panicked.

194
00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:45.000
So I jerked the car over and pulled out the map.

195
00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:50.000
And thankfully, for whatever reason, I'd been taken on a slightly different route to normal.

196
00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:54.000
That did pass through Florida, but I was right on track unbeknownst to me.

197
00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:58.000
Just being taken in a different direction than I thought.

198
00:15:58.000 --> 00:16:00.000
Why is the disciples having been following Jesus?

199
00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:01.000
They've got this shock.

200
00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:03.000
This is not how they had planned it.

201
00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:05.000
This is not what they thought would happen.

202
00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:10.000
But nonetheless, this movement that they were part of was not lost.

203
00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:15.000
It was just being brought about in a different way to how they had anticipated.

204
00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:19.000
Jesus' death was not an unfortunate turn of events.

205
00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:21.000
Notice that word that he uses.

206
00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:23.000
It was necessary.

207
00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:29.000
It was an essential part of God's plan to redeem the world.

208
00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:33.000
Now, while this plan wasn't something that they had anticipated,

209
00:16:33.000 --> 00:16:36.000
God had already revealed it in his word.

210
00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:47.000
So he goes on beginning with Moses and all the prophets were told that he interpreted to them and the scriptures and all the scriptures, the things concerning himself.

211
00:16:47.000 --> 00:16:51.000
I've heard some wonderful Bible teaching in my life.

212
00:16:51.000 --> 00:17:02.000
But if I could go and sit on any sermon, this is the one I would want to be in to have Jesus himself right along beside me, explaining the scriptures.

213
00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:10.000
And I would imagine being there with them and makes you wonder where he took them as he was opening the scriptures, telling them the things about himself and his suffering, his death.

214
00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:14.000
Maybe he told them about the prophecies that would be fulfilled.

215
00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:16.000
We're told that he began with Moses.

216
00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:20.000
So Moses is responsible for those first five books of the Bible.

217
00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:28.000
So maybe he took them to Genesis 315, which spoke about the coming Christ as being the one who would conquer the serpents.

218
00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:34.000
So he was going to suffer because of that serpent, but he was going to crush that serpent.

219
00:17:34.000 --> 00:17:49.000
Or maybe he took them to the prophets like Isaiah and Isaiah 53, where the coming Christ is presented as the suffering serpents, the one who was going to bear our iniquities,

220
00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:52.000
the one who was going to be wounded for our transgressions.

221
00:17:52.000 --> 00:18:00.000
Or maybe he took them to some of the types that were there in the Old Testament, some of those pictures that point to the coming of Christ.

222
00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:14.000
Maybe he talked to them about the Passover lamb and how when God sees the blood of the atoning sacrifice of Jesus, his judgment passes over us just like his judgment passed over the Israelites in Egypt.

223
00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:19.000
Maybe he talked to them about the temple where God's presence and glory dwelt among his people and said,

224
00:18:19.000 --> 00:18:23.000
well, that was pointing to me because I am God's presence with you.

225
00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:27.000
His glory is what I am here to make known.

226
00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:34.000
Well, it certainly seems that he talked them through the storyline of Scripture because he talked to them about all the Scriptures.

227
00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:37.000
Now they had a very short journey, so he had to be brief with them.

228
00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:47.000
Maybe talk to them about creation and how God made us for himself with a view to dwelling with us in perfect fellowship forever.

229
00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:55.000
Then of course there was the fall where we sinned against God and we rejected him and through sin, corruption and death came into the world.

230
00:18:55.000 --> 00:18:59.000
And worst of all, we were separated from God because of our sin.

231
00:18:59.000 --> 00:19:02.000
That relationship was broken.

232
00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:13.000
But God revealed that he had a plan of redemption that he was going to deal with our sin through sending this Messiah who would suffer and die in our place.

233
00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:26.000
Surely he pointed them as well to promises of restoration when one day we would dwell with God forever and we would feast with him in the new creation.

234
00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:39.000
I don't know exactly how he explained it, but I do know this, that he showed them that all of the Scriptures, all of it was pointing to him because he is our ultimate hope.

235
00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:51.000
In the Scriptures he is presented to us as the crucified and risen king who restores us to God and reigns over all things and welcomes all who will call upon him by faith.

236
00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:57.000
So we open the Scriptures to them because the Scriptures point them to Jesus and show who he is.

237
00:19:57.000 --> 00:20:08.000
But he also broke bread with them. When you come to verse 28, you see that when they arrived they invited Jesus to stay with them and to share a meal together which he agreed to.

238
00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:20.000
And as they sat at the table together, they deferred to this curious stranger to do the honor of breaking and our blessing rather and breaking the bread that was before them.

239
00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:29.000
By the way, meals are a major part in the Gospel of Luke if you look through that. It's amazing. Jesus is constantly eating with people.

240
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:35.000
And it's a wonderful way to do ministry, to share meals and life together.

241
00:20:35.000 --> 00:20:41.000
And there are times when it speaks about Jesus in these meals, blessing and breaking bread.

242
00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:50.000
So you go for example to the feeding of the 5,000. He blesses and he breaks the bread. God miraculously feeds the 5,000. He does.

243
00:20:50.000 --> 00:21:03.000
You look at the Last Supper before Jesus' death. We're told that he gathered with his disciples and he took bread and when he had given thanks he broke it and said, this is my body which is broken for you.

244
00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:08.000
So this is about more than food when Jesus breaks bread with people.

245
00:21:09.000 --> 00:21:15.000
This is the living embodiment of the very thing that Jesus came to bring about.

246
00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:22.000
When Jesus was sharing these meals with people, it was God himself dwelling with humanity.

247
00:21:22.000 --> 00:21:27.000
This was a picture of what was to come for all of God's people.

248
00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:37.000
And then when Jesus broke this bread before them, we're told that suddenly they recognized who he was.

249
00:21:37.000 --> 00:21:40.000
Then he vanished from their sight.

250
00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:48.000
See previously we're told in the passage that their eyes were kept from recognizing Jesus, but now they see him.

251
00:21:49.000 --> 00:21:52.000
This is a supernatural work.

252
00:21:52.000 --> 00:22:00.000
We can infer from this passage, but also the rest of scripture that God is the one who opened their eyes that they might see Jesus for who he truly is.

253
00:22:00.000 --> 00:22:10.000
Not with their physical eyes, but with the very eyes of their hearts. Yes they saw him with their physical eyes, but their hearts saw and knew who he was.

254
00:22:10.000 --> 00:22:15.000
So let me ask a question. Why was Jesus made known to them in this way?

255
00:22:15.000 --> 00:22:19.000
Why didn't he just tell them, this is who I am?

256
00:22:19.000 --> 00:22:25.000
Two things. One is that they might truly know who he is.

257
00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:33.000
If he had just immediately told them that he's Jesus, he's risen from the dead, they would have had relief, but they wouldn't have had true understanding.

258
00:22:33.000 --> 00:22:40.000
He wanted them to know that he was alive, yes, but he wanted them to understand who he truly was and what he came to do.

259
00:22:40.000 --> 00:22:44.000
And how essential he and his work was for God's plan.

260
00:22:44.000 --> 00:22:52.000
He wanted them to see what had been brought about through him, through his death and through his resurrection.

261
00:22:52.000 --> 00:22:58.000
He wanted to teach them through his word because they needed to continue to trust in his word throughout their lives.

262
00:22:58.000 --> 00:23:02.000
But this wasn't just true of them, it would be true of the people they would teach.

263
00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:06.000
So here's another reason why Jesus made himself known to them in this way.

264
00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:11.000
It's because that's how we all come to know Jesus.

265
00:23:11.000 --> 00:23:18.000
At the beginning I said that this same Jesus who drew near to them draws near to us.

266
00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:27.000
And you might very well think, well yeah, if Jesus physically walked up to me then I would believe, sure.

267
00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:31.000
But here we see that that's not how this works.

268
00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:39.000
And the fact is there were plenty of people who saw Jesus with their physical eyes and still rejected him.

269
00:23:39.000 --> 00:23:48.000
Here we see that Jesus made himself known to them in the Scriptures first because that is where he makes himself known to us.

270
00:23:48.000 --> 00:23:55.000
So this revelation that they saw with God's help we can see today as well.

271
00:23:55.000 --> 00:23:57.000
It's in the Scriptures that we can see Jesus.

272
00:23:57.000 --> 00:24:08.000
So one passage, 2 Timothy chapter 3 were told there that it's the Scriptures that make us wise to salvation through faith in Christ Jesus.

273
00:24:08.000 --> 00:24:11.000
And here's how we come to see Jesus in the Scriptures.

274
00:24:11.000 --> 00:24:15.000
Just like God opened their eyes, he opens our eyes so that we might see Jesus.

275
00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:22.000
That's how unbelievers are turned into believers because God opens their eyes to see Jesus.

276
00:24:22.000 --> 00:24:32.000
So Acts chapter 16 were told that the Lord opened the heart of a woman called Lydia so that she might hear and believe the Gospel.

277
00:24:32.000 --> 00:24:40.000
But you know, this is also how believers experience the reality of the risen Jesus too.

278
00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:49.000
In Ephesians 1 the apostle Paul prayed that God would enlighten the eyes of our hearts that we might know Jesus more

279
00:24:49.000 --> 00:24:52.000
and the hope that we have in him.

280
00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:58.000
So yes, God opens our eyes to believe in Jesus but there is always more to discover about him.

281
00:24:58.000 --> 00:25:04.000
We need to live in the reality of his risen life.

282
00:25:04.000 --> 00:25:07.000
And it's God who enables us to do this.

283
00:25:07.000 --> 00:25:13.000
And yet, that's not to say that we should just sit around waiting for that to happen.

284
00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:15.000
I'm just waiting for God to open my eyes to show me more.

285
00:25:15.000 --> 00:25:22.000
If God reveals himself in Scripture, if this is the place where we can come to see and know the risen Christ,

286
00:25:22.000 --> 00:25:28.000
then we ought to run to the Scriptures that we might see him and find the hope that is found in him.

287
00:25:28.000 --> 00:25:34.000
We ought to be praying, Lord, help me to see more of you here than I've ever seen.

288
00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:38.000
We should pray this for ourselves and pray this for others.

289
00:25:38.000 --> 00:25:41.000
This is how Jesus has made known to us.

290
00:25:41.000 --> 00:25:44.000
He's the hope that we need.

291
00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:48.000
We think about our vision for other things and maybe things not working out.

292
00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:54.000
What we need to see is Jesus and the greater thing that he is bringing about and how we can trust him.

293
00:25:54.000 --> 00:25:57.000
And the place we see him is in the Scriptures.

294
00:25:57.000 --> 00:26:04.000
Very briefly, the last thing I want us to see, thirdly, was the way that it changed these disciples.

295
00:26:04.000 --> 00:26:09.000
First, we see that it changed them on the inside.

296
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:14.000
I mean, we saw shock on their faces at the start, but there's shock now, but this is in a different way.

297
00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:19.000
The kind of sullen faces are now shocked that they have seen Jesus.

298
00:26:19.000 --> 00:26:21.000
I mean, they have been on quite the roller coaster.

299
00:26:21.000 --> 00:26:24.000
So listen to what they say in verse 32.

300
00:26:24.000 --> 00:26:32.000
Didn't our hearts burn within us while he talked with us on the road, while he opened to us the Scriptures?

301
00:26:32.000 --> 00:26:35.000
I mean, this was amazing what they had seen.

302
00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:42.000
And they knew that something was changing in them before they had even realized that this was Jesus who was speaking to them.

303
00:26:42.000 --> 00:26:50.000
Something was stirring in their hearts as Jesus was opening up the Scriptures to them and showing them his glory there.

304
00:26:50.000 --> 00:26:57.000
The embers of their hearts that were dying out were now being fanned into flame.

305
00:26:57.000 --> 00:27:04.000
You see, Jesus brings about an internal change as we begin to see who he truly is.

306
00:27:04.000 --> 00:27:09.000
And this is a change of mind and it is also a change of heart.

307
00:27:09.000 --> 00:27:18.000
We see and understand what the Scripture says, but then it teaches us to put our faith in him.

308
00:27:18.000 --> 00:27:30.000
So God then takes these glorious truths of the Scriptures about Jesus and uses them in our lives to teach us to trust again, to rejoice again,

309
00:27:30.000 --> 00:27:37.000
and to hope again because our hope is in Jesus.

310
00:27:37.000 --> 00:27:42.000
And that burning that takes place in their hearts, notice, it now starts to come through.

311
00:27:42.000 --> 00:27:46.000
What's happening on the inside now comes through on the outside.

312
00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:53.000
You know, after the burning to think about the space shovel again, after the burning then comes the lift off, right?

313
00:27:53.000 --> 00:28:02.000
So you've got these burning hearts, but that burning heart is soon heard by a speaking mouth and running feet.

314
00:28:02.000 --> 00:28:09.000
Verse 32, they immediately start to talk to each other about what it is that they've heard and what it is they've seen.

315
00:28:09.000 --> 00:28:15.000
And then it hits them that they've got to go back and tell the other disciples that Jesus is alive.

316
00:28:15.000 --> 00:28:18.000
And remember, this is getting near the end of the day.

317
00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:22.000
We're giving that little detail as they talked with Jesus.

318
00:28:22.000 --> 00:28:27.000
By the time they got to Emmaus, they were seven miles away from Jerusalem.

319
00:28:27.000 --> 00:28:32.000
And those roads were dark and dangerous at night, but that did not hold them back.

320
00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:36.000
They had good news to share that they could not hold in.

321
00:28:36.000 --> 00:28:40.000
So they ran back to the disciples declaring that Jesus is alive.

322
00:28:40.000 --> 00:28:43.000
They don't waste any time getting back to Jerusalem.

323
00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:46.000
They return in the same hour, we're told.

324
00:28:46.000 --> 00:28:52.000
When they found those disciples, they joined together with them celebrating the resurrection of Jesus,

325
00:28:52.000 --> 00:29:02.000
saying, as we said at the start of the service, verse 34, the Lord is risen in deed.

326
00:29:02.000 --> 00:29:09.000
The fact is when the risen Christ draws near to you in your discouragement,

327
00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:13.000
and he starts to stir your heart and show you more of himself,

328
00:29:13.000 --> 00:29:18.000
the way that comes through is a desire to confess that he is Lord,

329
00:29:18.000 --> 00:29:23.000
to praise him with your mouth, to speak about him to others.

330
00:29:23.000 --> 00:29:28.000
Your heart overflows in your words. That desire is there.

331
00:29:28.000 --> 00:29:36.000
It gives you a desire to be in the company of those who are also celebrating and hoping in his resurrection.

332
00:29:36.000 --> 00:29:40.000
So that is why we're here today, because Jesus is alive.

333
00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:49.000
And we want to express that in our praise to him, but we want to do that together because he is worthy.

334
00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:56.000
You see, this is more than just optimism. This is more than just a little bit of inspiration.

335
00:29:56.000 --> 00:30:02.000
We have a living hope, and his name is Jesus.

336
00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:04.000
So let's return back to where we begin.

337
00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:09.000
Wherever you are in your journey.

338
00:30:09.000 --> 00:30:15.000
You're questioning, weary or energized.

339
00:30:15.000 --> 00:30:20.000
Know that Jesus is near.

340
00:30:20.000 --> 00:30:27.000
The risen Christ invites you into a relationship with himself.

341
00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:34.000
The hope that he gives is a hope that lasts forever because he lives and reigns forever more.

342
00:30:34.000 --> 00:30:41.000
So let's join together in celebrating and declaring that the Lord is risen indeed.

343
00:30:41.000 --> 00:30:44.000
We're going to come to him in prayer now. Let me pray.

344
00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:50.000
But then as I finish in prayer, just continue in prayer to the Lord where you're at.

345
00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:57.000
Wherever you're at, come to him.

346
00:30:57.000 --> 00:31:06.000
God, we want to praise you that Jesus came into this world, that he died to bring us back to you.

347
00:31:06.000 --> 00:31:12.000
He is risen from the dead. He reconciles us with yourself.

348
00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:19.000
Lord, we thank you that through the presence of the Spirit, he is here even now.

349
00:31:19.000 --> 00:31:27.000
Lord, I pray that even in this moment that we would each come to you by faith, hearing you calling us to yourself.

350
00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:34.000
Help us to know that you're near and to come to you in faith.

351
00:31:34.000 --> 00:31:42.000
And know the hope that is found in you and in you alone as we surrender ourselves to you.

352
00:31:42.000 --> 00:31:45.000
Our glorious risen King.

353
00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:47.000
Amen.

